Sentencas: Screen-printing technology was developed to fabricate gas-tight yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte films on porous NiO-YSZ anode substrates for use in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: A study of the process parameters for yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte films prepared by screen-printing

Sentencas: Several key process parameters such as the starting YSZ powder, printing ink composition, printing time and sintering temperature were studied and reported in detail.
Titulo: A study of the process parameters for yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte films prepared by screen-printing

Sentencas: SEM results revealed that the selected process parameters exerted obvious influences on the microstructure of the screen-printed YSZ films.
Titulo: A study of the process parameters for yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte films prepared by screen-printing

Sentencas: Open-circuit voltages (OCVs) were used to evaluate the usage feasibility of screen-printed YSZ films in SOFCs.
Titulo: A study of the process parameters for yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte films prepared by screen-printing

Sentencas: Cell performance test results showed that the above-mentioned parameters had crucial effects on the OCVs and power density of the prepared cells.
Titulo: A study of the process parameters for yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte films prepared by screen-printing

Sentencas: Based on appropriate parameters, an OCV value of 1.081 V and a power density of 0.96 Wcm(-2) were obtained at 800 degrees C using hydrogen as fuel and ambient air as oxidant.
Titulo: A study of the process parameters for yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte films prepared by screen-printing
